## AI System Rules & Best Practices

### ğŸ” Security & Configuration

#### DO:
- âœ… **Always use server-side AI calls** - All AI functions must use `'use server'` directive
- âœ… **Keep API keys in `.env.local`** - Never commit actual API keys to version control
- âœ… **Use environment variables** - `GOOGLE_API_KEY` for authentication
- âœ… **Validate AI inputs** - Always validate data before sending to AI models
- âœ… **Handle AI errors gracefully** - Provide fallback responses for AI failures

#### DON'T:
- âŒ **Never expose API keys client-side** - AI calls must be server-side only
- âŒ **Don't hardcode AI responses** - Use dynamic AI generation
- âŒ **Don't skip error handling** - AI services can fail, always handle gracefully
- âŒ **Don't bypass validation** - Always validate inputs before AI processing

